---
name: scljet-write-multitable
description: SclJet multi-table database — several rowid tables in one file, each at its own root page (cross-backend)
backends: [int, js]
---

# SclJet multi-table writer

[ByteSlice, byteSliceToList, SqliteValue, SqlInteger, SqlText, TableSpec, buildMultiTableDatabase](std/scljet/index.ssc)

```scalascript
// Three rowid tables in one file. Page 1 is sqlite_schema with a CREATE TABLE
// entry per table (each with its own root page), then each table's B-tree occupies
// a contiguous page range in declaration order. Reference integrity_check accepts
// the file and every table reads back exact; int and JS produce the same bytes.
val tables = List(
  TableSpec("users", "CREATE TABLE users(id INTEGER, name TEXT)",
    List(List(SqlInteger(1L), SqlText("alice")), List(SqlInteger(2L), SqlText("bob")))),
  TableSpec("products", "CREATE TABLE products(sku INTEGER, title TEXT)",
    List(List(SqlInteger(100L), SqlText("widget")), List(SqlInteger(200L), SqlText("gadget")), List(SqlInteger(300L), SqlText("gizmo")))),
  TableSpec("orders", "CREATE TABLE orders(oid INTEGER, total INTEGER)",
    List(List(SqlInteger(1L), SqlInteger(4200L)))))

buildMultiTableDatabase(512, 1, 1, tables) match
  case Right(bytes) => println((bytes.length / 512).toString + ":" + byteSliceToList(bytes).toString)
  case Left(error) => println("ERROR:" + error.message)
```
